               <lb n="2"/><w>κα<unclear>ὶ</unclear></w> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>	
               <lb n="3"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="Κρίσπος"><seg part="I">Κρισ<unclear>π</unclear></seg></name></persName><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
               <lb n="4"/><space quantity="1" unit="character"/> <w part="I">ἥρω</w><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
            </ab>
         </div>
         
         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> I... ? and (? dedicated a statue of)... ? Crispus... hero</p>
         </div>
         
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>It is not clear whether what survives of the text named one person or two; if one, then a man/boy is named in line 1, the name perhaps continuing in lines2-3,
               and in line 4 he is described as a hero; if two, the first name, beginning in line 1 probably named as a hero the man or boy described by the second 
               (whose beginning we cannot assess, but <foreign xml:lang="grc">ΚΡΙΣΠ<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></foreign>, 
               probably Crispus, is likely to be his cognomen).  
            </p>
            <p>For heroization in the Sanctuary cf. <ref type="inscription">C90700</ref><!--A.38-->.</p>
         </div>
